snippet.textDisplay:
Yes, I am sure Brad feels the weight of the pain he caused Jen. I mean all his friends told him not to do it but he just wouldn't listen. Now they are around each other all the time and of course Jen is looking hotter than ever. I mean if you listen to Ethan Hawke when he talks about kissing Angie on the set of their movie, he says it was like she had a hold on him. It is nothing he ever experienced. It was electric and he said it was intoxicating.

I am not saying that Brad didn't have a choice but there is a reason women in Hollywood didn't allow their husbands to work with Angie. She is still not well liked. Jen trusted Brad and didn't feel intimidated by Angie...big mistake. But it is the aftermath that shakes me. They went on with their lives calling it falling in love on the set and flaunting their relationship in front of Jen who was clearly in pain. Angie saw what she wanted and went after him. Mr. and Mrs. Smith was an intense movie. It didn't matter that Jen and Brad had a great friendship and a marriage. Angie then dated him for 10 years having three children and Brad adopting three of her kids. On magazine covers everywhere. Brad married her because the children wanted to know why they weren't married yet. So Angie after breaking up her third marriage and having six children with the hottest man in Hollywood, she still couldn't keep him and he turns to drinking because of course he has now you are raising six kids, you have regrets and guilt.

Jen also went on to marry again and I think she was happy for a little while but I don't think she really let Justin in. Don't get me wrong I do love Brad but there are certainly consequences for his decisions and actions. If I were Jen I would be careful with that friendship. No one knows what the future really holds for Jen and Brad if the love is still there. I have seen couples that have gone through worst find their way back to each other.

snippet.textDisplay:
I just think we all wished Jen and Brad would get back together, sometimes you need distance and then one or both realizes that they should have stayed together. He I think realizes now he hurt her and the depth of that hurt. He had his children with Angie and I was gonna keep this tasteless magazine cover to kind of keep showing what a jerk he was but decided not to, he did with Angelina when they were having the affair or soon after they separated when he left her for Angie and shows him sitting at this table with about 6 blonde kids and Angie and him as the parents. It was his “genius” idea I am sure Angie also thought it would be great. It was in such bad taste. Angie’s natural hair is also blonde. Her biological kids look just like her. They say Brad looks like them but I think they favor her a bunch too. So it was a self fulfilling project, lots of kids and 3 look like both of them.

I remember Jen being devastated when asked if she thought he left her over not having kids and Angie being pregnant, she said she did not think he would hurt her like that and she did not want to believe Angie was pregnant and that the cover was hurtful since he has decided to do it that way, and then boom! we all next see Angie obviously pregnant on a beach with him. I also cringed at how Angie acted with her when she introduced herself she said she was so excited her husband was working with her on set I watched the stage 5 Klingon way Angie was holding in to him on set on mr and mrs smith film, when it was not necessary because they were not in scene. It was so obvious, she had this way of being this needy sexual person. If you watch this old movie she did with billy Bob where her character plays that and cheats on her husband I think she in real life is a lot like that character in that she focuses her whole attention in like worshiping and being very sexual with men she pursuits.

I thought to myself “ruh roh” when I saw her leaning in and holding his hand, and I was like what the hell, they are nit filming! I remembered how a similar thing happened to me when I helped someone in the film industry and they helped themself right into helping themselves to my relationship break up. I was trusting like Jen and so naive like Jenifer. I was so confident I was not threatened by the witch that I helped immensely.

Even my sweet kind friend who never even said a curse works, warned me she wants to take what you have. She is threatened by you and this is a game to her. Maybe I was crazy because I did not feel intimidated by her mentally or physically but then I started seeing the signs, my vindication was his calling and complaining and even the bitch called me when I was sick and starts asking my mother about my health issues, I told her you have a question ask me because my maman is a Louisiana woman and although sweet when it comes to her kids she is gonna visit you trust and believe me she is a very physically strong woman and you should have heard my maman say how dare that “Putain se merde” call me, lol. And many other curse words flew. And my maman is not on the French side but she grew up around my defan papa and many wonderful cajun people and even looks like them. So she was knows the phrases. Nothing worse than a Cajun getting fashay/angry because we are most such good and friendly people and will help just about anyone.

She was freaked out because clearly he regretted being with her and she knew if I was sick he was gonna use that as an excuse to try and talk to me and one day he flew to see me without my knowledge he was coming I answered the door and said hey you need to go home to her, because I am not at all interested in your little pattern of doing what you do after you make a selfish decision. She left him later for a younger guy. He called again to cry over that. He said she cursed him with some witches type curse and I said maybe this is because you di what you did to me, cause my old nanan did have a vodou doll on your ass! Lol! I have a great story about when she had vodou doll and it worked! I think Jen has enough confidence in herself although she probably has deep hurt that she will not take him back.

He would have to do a lot of groveling and public assurances to get her to consider that and I don’t think she will. She has enough confidence and she also had deep hurt, and truly loved him. He was an idiot and frankly I hated that my old boyfriend would cry like that in public to get attention. It disgusted me. It disgusted his friends who called me and said he has messed up losing you and we are nit going to let him manipulate us. We told him he effed up! Brad was selfish and he lusted after Angie and Angie was every bit selfish breaking up marriages as she did with billy Bob too. What makes her like that after she talks about her father cheating is beyond my own understanding. I would think she knew the damage she caused and the hurt. I do think she is beautiful but I can’t like her. She is selfish. And she wants everyone to think she is some angel because she is involved with adoption and charity work. Strikes me as pretentious.

So maybe he realizes he messed up. Maybe. My exes all cry like that. With good reason haha! I am very kind and very nurturing and I cook fantastic cajun and southern comfort food. I used to have all his office ask to eat my food because we had a business where film people worked and stopped by. And I helped them with their careers, my ex had never acted except one extra role and I got him and audition with this famous animator he worships and he booked the male lead role. He just has to play himself a whiny entitled brat! He was such a prima Donna it was hilarious as he thought he was some brilliant talent. Even the director laughed with me about how he just wanted him because he really acts that way in real life. And I helped him book another job posing in front f a computer. He refused to cut his hair after he had given a head shot with shorter hair snd glasses. He looked terrible in that he was really thin and older so he looked really bad with long hair. He has weak features and looked so much better with it shorter. Without me being an agent he would have been ignored, I had to push him to be picked, WW had two lists and he was on 2nd so when they could not book the guy they wanted they listened to me. I was furious he would not cut his hair.

His friends would smell my cooking. I usually feed them morning time. Had biscuits and breakfast foods. omelette are my specialty but wish I could flip crepes like my defan papa. I would introduce them to cajun chicory cafe and cafe au lait which my daddy made which is cajun coffee with steamed milk.
So we had this guy that kind of made me angry and was rude because of my friendliness end up staying for dinner one night when I was cooking cajun game hens. He was a great cinematographer though and basically he kept saying how good it smelled cause I used a cajun “Tony Sachere’s “ recipe. My defan papa like all Louisiana men was so good at cooking and table presentation I think he would have written a cook book and opened his own restaurant. And had a cooking show. All the Louisiana men I know are great cooks. They enjoy doing it. He made everything from cajun seafood to southern comfort and blackened fish to pralines and divinity and pies. I love making pies and we had a pie contest. He was so competitive! Lol. If I cooked he would say well it was alright! Lol! I miss him.

My ex’s friend said his wife was from England and could not cook like me cause it is how we use the spices not how hot is is, that makes cajun and creole and spanish indien food like zwolle tamales good, and he had lived in Texas and yet never had Louisiana food. He said she never seasoned anything. He went crazy over it and once he understood Louisiana French and spanish indien people are friendly he was nice. He kept saying he did not want to intrude and I would say we have plenty “pas no problem” so no worries.

I am glad he realized my hospitality and kindness were from a “real” place. I always laugh at my “Hollywood and film industry and music industry friends saying I am so real. I think well of course I am. He also complimented me when we worked on a very stressful set together he and the crew said without me the production would and could not have been a success. I swear that just about floored me and I was stressed to the max. I had to put my foot down. At times I was not so nice when people acted up.

So anyway, that is my take I hope he does realize how wonderful she was and is. He really screwed up. Of course he has beautiful children but he learned I think, at least I hope he did. And I don’t think Angie did but I hope she learned there are consequences for breaking up a marriage, I hope some of the pain she caused Jenifer she felt when they broke up. Because maybe that pain will cause her not to do it again nor encourage her kids to. I just wish she would find out why she has to do that. She just focuses all her attention on the man yet also makes them feel she is sooo needy. I guess they like that. I don’t like insecure people they may be attracted to you but in the end they try and destroy you. It is one kind of weird phenomenon that I noticed in males and females. I think ole Brad got taste of what happens when they flip the switch on you when Angie did it to him!

She was freaked out because clearly he regretted being with her and she knew if I was sick he was gonna use that as an excuse to try and talk to me and one day he flew to see me without my knowledge he was coming I answered the door and said hey you need to go home to her, because I am not at all interested in your little pattern of doing what you do after you make a selfish decision. She left him later for a younger guy. He called again to cry over that. He said she cursed him with some witches type curse and I said maybe this is because you di what you did to me, cause my old nanan did have a vodou doll on your ass! Lol! I have a great story about when she had vodou doll and it worked! I think Jen has enough confidence in herself although she probably has deep hurt that she will not take him back. 

He would have to do a lot of groveling and public assurances to get her to consider that and I don’t think she will. She has enough confidence and she also had deep hurt, and truly loved him. He was an idiot and frankly I hated that my old boyfriend would cry like that in public to get attention. It disgusted me. It disgusted his friends who called me and said he has messed up losing you and we are nit going to let him manipulate us. We told him he effed up! Brad was selfish and he lusted after Angie and Angie was every bit selfish breaking up marriages as she did with billy Bob too. What makes her like that after she talks about her father cheating is beyond my own understanding. I would think she knew the damage she caused and the hurt. I do think she is beautiful but I can’t like her. She is selfish. And she wants everyone to think she is some angel because she is involved with adoption and charity work. Strikes me as pretentious. 

So maybe he realizes he messed up. Maybe. My exes all cry like that. With good reason haha! I am very kind and very nurturing and I cook fantastic cajun and southern comfort food. I used to have all his office ask to eat my food because we had a business where film people worked and stopped by. And I helped them with their careers, my ex had never acted except one extra role and I got him and audition with this famous animator he worships and he booked the male lead role. He just has to play himself a whiny entitled brat! He was such a prima Donna it was hilarious as he thought he was some brilliant talent. Even the director laughed with me about how he just wanted him because he really acts that way in real life. And I helped him book another job posing in front f a computer. He refused to cut his hair after he had given a head shot  with shorter hair snd glasses. He looked terrible in that he was really thin and older so he looked really bad with long hair. He has weak features and looked so much better with it shorter. Without me being an agent he would have been ignored, I had to push him to be picked, WW had two lists and he was on 2nd so when they could not book the guy they wanted they listened to me. I was furious he would not cut his hair. 

His friends would smell my cooking. I usually feed them morning time. Had biscuits and breakfast foods. omelette are my specialty but wish I could flip crepes like my defan papa. I would introduce them to cajun chicory cafe and cafe au lait which my daddy made which is cajun coffee with steamed milk.  
So we had this guy that kind of made me angry and was rude because of my friendliness end up staying for dinner one night when I was cooking cajun game hens. He was a great cinematographer  though and basically he kept saying how good it smelled cause I used a cajun “Tony Sachere’s “ recipe. My defan papa like all Louisiana men was so good at cooking and table presentation I think he would have written a cook book and opened his own restaurant. And had a cooking show. All the Louisiana men I know are great cooks. They enjoy doing it. He made everything from cajun seafood to southern comfort and blackened fish to pralines and divinity and pies. I love making pies and we had a pie contest. He was so competitive! Lol. If I cooked he would say well it was alright! Lol! I miss him. 

 My ex’s friend said his wife was from England and could not cook like me cause it is how we use the spices not how hot is is, that makes cajun and creole and spanish indien food like zwolle tamales good, and he had lived in Texas and yet never had Louisiana food. He said she never seasoned anything. He went crazy over it and once he understood Louisiana French and spanish indien people are friendly he was nice. He kept saying he did not want to intrude and I would say we have plenty “pas no problem” so no worries. 

I am glad he realized my hospitality and kindness were from a “real” place. I always laugh at my “Hollywood and film industry and music industry friends saying I am so real. I think well of course I am. He also complimented me when we worked on a very stressful set together he and the crew said without me the production would and could not have been a success. I swear that just about floored me and I was stressed to the max. I had to put my foot down. At times I was not so nice when people acted up. 

So anyway, that is my take I hope he does realize how wonderful she was and is. He really screwed up. Of course he has beautiful children but he learned I think, at least I hope he did. And I don’t think Angie did but I hope she learned there are consequences for breaking up a marriage, I hope some of the pain she caused Jenifer she felt when they broke up. Because maybe that pain will cause her not to do it again nor encourage her kids to. I just wish she would find out why she has to do that. She just focuses all her attention on the man yet also makes them feel she is sooo needy. I guess they like that. I don’t like insecure people they may be attracted to you but in the end they try and destroy you. It is one kind of weird phenomenon that I noticed in males and females. I think ole Brad got taste of what happens when they flip the switch on you when Angie did it to him!
